import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot([data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']['precipitation'], data[data['location'] == 'New York']['precipitation']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Seattle', 'New York'], rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    seattle = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    new_york = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.plot(seattle['date'], seattle['temp_max'], label='Seattle Max Temp')
    ax.plot(seattle['date'], seattle['temp_min'], label='Seattle Min Temp')
    ax.plot(new_york['date'], new_york['temp_max'], label='New York Max Temp')
    ax.plot(new_york['date'], new_york['temp_min'], label='New York Min Temp')
    ax.set_title('How does the temperature vary in Seattle and New York over time?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['precipitation'], c=pd.factorize(data['location'])[0], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(pd.factorize(data['location'])[1])
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    weather_count = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    seattle_weather = weather_count[weather_count['location'] == 'Seattle']
    ny_weather = weather_count[weather_count['location'] == 'New York']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.bar(seattle_weather['weather'], seattle_weather['counts'], label='Seattle')
    ax.bar(ny_weather['weather'], ny_weather['counts'], label='New York')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
